name: Eclectic design home, super central
description: Discount on longer stays - Super central location in walking distance to central station. Creative design apartment in a classic building with original floor and details. With a cosy balcony! Centrally located in the eastern part of the city Grønland/Tøyen/Gamlebyen, in a neighbourhood that is colorful and diverse with foreign grocery stores and funky hipster cafes and restaurants. Appeared in several interior design magazines and TV programs.
neighborhood_overview: A very central location on the east side of town at Grønland/Tøyen. This is a diverse and colorful part of town. Trendy and up and coming. A lot of nice places to explore in the neigbourhood, Munch Museum, Botanical Garden, the main street at Gronland has many cool places to go out and grab a bite to eat. Also close to the Ekeberg sculpture park and the BARCODE area where the Opera house. If you want to live where the high end fashion stores are, you need to get a location on the west side. :) In my neighbourhood you find the best indian curry dishes! Great beer places! And the best backyard gardens to go party in in the evening or enjoy a good lunch.
host_about:
A creative urban girl from Oslo, but a citizen of the world. 41 years old. Love to travel, see new places and meet new people. And I think Airbnb is such a great way to explore the world. 
 
Designer by heart. Working as a freelance as a Photographer, Content Creator, Social Media Manager and graphic designer. 
 
My other interest: Architecture, design, foodie, music, art and culture. 
 
I love my city and would be more than happy to share tips on where to go and what to do here in town. If you are planning a trip to Norway with more stops than Oslo, let me know. I am happy to help you plan your trip with great tips on things to see and do in our beautiful country.

Welcome to this unique and creative apartment in the heart of Grünerløkka, Oslo!

Grocery store just across the street and minutes to tram, subway and bus. Experience charming Rodeløkka as well as the lively diversity of Grünerløkka with restaurants and shops.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in Rodeløkka, a charming historic neighborhood with a village atmosphere in the middle of the city. name: Bright and Cozy 2BR Flat in Oslo
description: Welcome to our sunny 2BR flat in Oslo's hipster district, Grünerløkka! A 10-minute walk from the city center and central station, our 80 m² flat is surrounded by top restaurants. Enjoy a king-size bed, cot bed for children, and a luxurious sofa bed. The kitchen is fully equipped, with a large fridge and freezer. Stream your favorites with Google Chromecast. Includes WiFi, a bathroom with tub, and quality linens. Quiet, secure, with parks and the Aker nearby. Elevator and bike-friendly backyard.

Love Get-togethers and asados with my friends and every now and then I must play 11-a-side.
I'm rediscovering reading all over again.
I identify myself with sitcom character Chandler Muriel Bing.

name: Scandi-style relaxing apartment
description:
Come enjoy a stay at this cozy 2-bedroom apartment at central and hip Grünerløkka.

The apartment is bright and airy and has everything you need in your everyday life. Multiple supermarkets, transport options, restaurants, cafes and shops all within a few blocks and the city center at walking distance. The nearby and beautiful Aker river offers a great green option for a stroll or a drink.

The building complex has a large shared garden where guests can BBQ, dine and hang out.

Welcome :)
